-- Peru Stocks: Alturas, Credicorp, Minera IRL, Southern Copper
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-10T18:48:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/peru-stocks-alturas-credicorp-minera-irl-southern-copper.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:21 p.m.  New York  time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  gained 1.2 percent to 20,193.02. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  climbed 1.5 percent to 2,604.15.  Banks and industrial shares gained amid a global rally in
equities, said Inteligo SAB portfolio manager Gonzalo Alvarez.  Credicorp Ltd. (BAP)  , Peru’s largest financial-services
company, rose 3.7 percent to $108.50.  Corp. Aceros Arequipa SA (CORA) 
(CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, climbed 2.1 percent to
1.97 soles.  Grana y Montero SA  (GRAMONC1 PE), Peru’s largest
construction firm, gained 2 percent to 6.73 soles.  Scotiabank
Peru SA (SCOTIAC1)  (SCOTIAC1 PE), the local unit of  Canada ’s third-largest
bank, rose 1.4 percent to 36.50 soles.  Miners surged after metals advanced in New York and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, rose 11 percent to 10 cents.  Rio Cristal
Resources Corp. (RCZ)  , a Canadian exploration company, gained
10 percent to 11 cents.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. gold
miner with a mine in Peru, advanced 5.9 percent to $1.08.  Panoro
Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian exploration company, climbed
5 percent to 42 cents.  Southern Copper Corp. (PCU\C)  (SCCO PE), Peru’s
biggest copper producer, rose 2.8 percent to $31.83.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
